I"K<p>Install kramdown and rouge</p>
<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>gem install kramdown rouge
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Find available rouge syntax-highlighting style</p>
<div class="language-java highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="n">rougify</span> <span class="n">help</span> <span class="n">style</span>
</code></pre></div></div>
<p>Preview for various rouge styles  <br />
https://spsarolkar.github.io/rouge-theme-preview/</p>

<p>Create syntax-highlighting file (monokai style for example)</p>
<div class="language-java highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="n">rougify</span> <span class="n">style</span> <span class="n">monokai</span> <span class="o">&gt;</span> <span class="o">/</span><span class="n">css</span><span class="o">/</span><span class="n">syntax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="na">css</span>
</code></pre></div></div>
<p>And copy and paste all the codes in the ‘syntax.css’ file to where you think appropriate</p>
